      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): surface inbound startup diagnostics",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add default-level, privacy-safe diagnostics when inbound rows are dropped for echo/reflection reasons (`echo`, `self-chat echo`, `agent echo in self-chat`, `reflected assistant content`). The log includes account, reason, numeric chat id when present, row/message id, GUID presence, group flag, and timestamp, but not message text, sender handles, or full GUIDs.\n- Add structured `watch.subscribe` startup retry/failure context: account, `cliPath`, db path presence, remote-host presence, timeout, `since_rowid`, attachment/reaction flags, attempt count, and retry delay.\n- Keep this diagnostics-only: no inbound delivery policy, watch retry classification, retry count, teardown, or thrown error behavior changes.\n\nRefs #89593.\nRefs #87263.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/imessage/src/monitor.watch-subscribe-retry.test.ts` (4 tests)\n- `pnpm format:check -- extensions/imessage/src/monitor/monitor-provider.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.watch-subscribe-retry.test.ts`\n- `pnpm lint:extensions -- extensions/imessage/src/monitor/monitor-provider.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.watch-subscribe-retry.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --prompt \"Review this diagnostics-only iMessage monitor patch. It should not change inbound delivery policy or watch.subscribe retry behavior. Focus on log noise/privacy, whether echo/reflection drops are surfaced without message content/sender handles, whether watch.subscribe retry/failure diagnostics include useful startup context, and whether tests cover the new formatting.\"` (clean)\n\n## Current proof gap\n\nThis PR intentionally does not claim a behavior fix for either issue. It adds the missing evidence needed to distinguish these cases in the next live repro:\n\n- #89593: whether the inbound row is being classified as echo/self-chat/reflection versus failing before the normal decision path.\n- #87263: whether `watch.subscribe` is timing out with a specific startup configuration (`cliPath`, db path, `since_rowid`, timeout, remote/local bridge shape).\n\nA broader local run of `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/imessage/src/monitor.watch-subscribe-retry.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor/inbound-processing.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor/self-chat-dedupe.test.ts` currently fails in the untouched `inbound-processing.test.ts` expectation for the echo-cache options object. The touched retry diagnostics test passes.\n",
        "branch": "fix/imessage-inbound-startup-diagnostics",
